{"id":30792,"date":"2018-12-05T07:24:11","date_gmt":"2018-12-04T21:24:11","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=30792"},"modified":"2021-10-14T14:59:38","modified_gmt":"2021-10-14T04:59:38","slug":"new-act-190-nomination-program","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/new-act-190-nomination-program\/","title":{"rendered":"New ACT\u2019s 190 nomination program effective 29 November 2018"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]The <strong>subclass 190<\/strong> is a permanent resident visa for points-tested skilled workers who wish to work and live in Australia. Being nominated by an Australian State or Territory Government Agency is a threshold requirement for this visa. Each state and territory have their unique program and requirements but the maximum number of nominations which they can make is determined by the Department of Home Affairs.<\/p>\n<p>On 29 November 2018 the Australian Capital Territory reopened its 190-nomination program with a<strong> new expression of interest process<\/strong>. The new program will continue focusing on specific state occupation shortages but will replace its previous first-in\/first-out process with a <strong>merit-based <\/strong>approach.<\/p>\n<p>The new system will allow intending applicants to express their interest through the <strong>score-based<\/strong> \u201c<strong>Canberra Matrix\u201d<\/strong>. The State Government will periodically select those applicants who based on their points are of economic benefit to Canberra.<\/p>\n<p>Points are allocated based on different factors such as English language proficiency, nominated occupation, employment, qualifications, close family ties to Canberra etc.<\/p>\n<p>Additionally, before applicants can express their interest in ACT 190 nomination, they must meet certain criteria which varies depending on whether they are Canberra residents or overseas applicants. Common requirements include demonstrable Proficiency level of English and genuine commitment to live in Canberra for at least two years.<\/p>\n<p>Some <strong>key aspects<\/strong> of the new ACT 190 nomination program include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Canberra Matrix scores are ranked against each other and only candidates with the higher points will be invited to apply for state nomination.<\/li>\n<li>The ACT government will not respond to individual requests for ranking information nor will prioritise or issue invitations based on personal circumstances such as current visa expiring etc.<\/li>\n<li>The Canberra Matrix cannot be amended upon submission so if the candidate\u2019s circumstances change a new Canberra Matrix must be submitted.<\/li>\n<li>After an invitation is issued and the subsequent application is lodged, additional supporting documents will not be accepted. This also means that there will be no request for further information from the case officer and the nomination may be refused if the documentation provided is incomplete or does not evidence the Canberra Matrix score on invitation.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Threshold requirements, the Canberra Matrix scoring system and information regarding the nomination process are available on the ACT Nomination guidelines <a href=\"http:\/\/www.canberrayourfuture.com.au\/portal\/migrating\/article\/skilled-visa-act-190-nomination\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a> <i class=\"icon-Right-4\"><\/i>.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][nectar_global_section id=&#8221;109315&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221;&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":59828,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[88,118,129],"tags":[],"class_list":{"0":"post-30792","1":"post","2":"type-post","3":"status-publish","4":"format-standard","5":"has-post-thumbnail","7":"category-act","8":"category-migration-program","9":"category-skilled-visa"},"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/30792","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=30792"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/30792\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":109387,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/30792\/revisions\/109387"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/59828"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=30792"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=30792"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=30792"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}